Acron Asks Putin to Bar Silvinit, Uralkali Deal, Vedomosti Says

-- B y   H e n r y   M e y e r
-- 
2011-02-18T09:58:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/acron-asks-putin-to-bar-silvinit-uralkali-deal-vedomosti-says.html
OAO Acron, Russia’s third-largest
nitrogen-fertilizer maker, has asked Prime Minister  Vladimir Putin  to forbid a merger between potash producers OAO Uralkali
and OAO Silvinit, Vedomosti reported, citing a copy of a letter
sent to Putin.  Acron also asked Putin to order the Federal Anti-Monopoly
Service to deny Uralkali’s application to merge with Silvinit,
the Moscow-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henry Meyer in Moscow at 
 hmeyer4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net  